top.value: Action Against Hunger will strive to reduce mortality and morbidity in the communities of the Alindao-Mingala Health District through the improvement of secondary health care and water, hygiene and sanitation conditions at the Alindao District Hospital.

This humanitarian project is proposing to both assist the population with emergency intervention in acute nutrition crisis and address consequences of nutrition crisis in areas identified by the consortium where a multi-year approach could improve the nutrition and health status of under 5 children and pregnant and lactating women
ACF response in Cholera outbreak in Kemo (CAR)

ACF started to intervene 5 days after the first joint assessment distributing WASH kits to ensure the access to drinking water and capacities to contain it, sensitization have been made to ensure hygiene promotion. Active screenings were carried out referencing MAS cases in OTP/ ITFC (every 2 weeks) and follow-up is done through home visit when necessary. During the follow-up, the Mental Health & Care Practices (MHCP) is associated (workshop of entrance / workshop of exit / session of relaxation).

A continuation of SHARP (a previous programme under the BRCiS Consortium) 

BRCiS contributes to the resilience pillar but also to the human rights, agriculture, livestock and fisheries, economic development and the Social and Human Development pillars. The Consortium commits to align to the National Development Plans vision and goals and to actively coordinate with the relevant Federal Institutions when there are targeted actions that will build community capacity to achieve these goals

Action Against Hunger is pleased to sign this call of interest for EAP Custodian Process in Zimbabwe alongside its local partner, Nutrition Action Zimbabwe, a registered Private Voluntary Organization (PVO 38/19) working in Zimbabwe, which aims to meet the immediate and long-termfood and nutrition needs of targeted communities and building their resilience to respond to repeated shocks.

Action Against Hunger and local partners will evaluate the integration of WaterScopes bacterial testing system for drinking water into ongoing programmes in Ethiopia and Kenya to improve decision-making on water supply.

Action Against Hunger partner will provide humanitarian assistance to at least 500 households from Nagorno-Karabakh who were displaced in Armenia. Action Against Hunger will contract supermarkets in the respective locations where the vouchers can be used by the beneficiaries.

AAH will initiate activities in Odessa and Mykolaiv in order to gradually expand programmatic reach in the South while building on existing work in the East, in particular around Kharkiv. The strategy for Odessa and Mykolaiv will be to utilise AAH Spains presence in Moldova and existing partnerships and logistical capacity. In the initial months, AAH Spain will conduct cross-border operations through its partners in Moldova and Odessa. AAH Spain and AAH France have planned a joint assessment in October (security permitting) to kick-start interventions, update understanding of the needs, strengthen partner relationships in Odessa, and prepare for a longer-term presence.
